<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>JAMAICAN VACATION</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20070823.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<div id='gazette_byline''><em>By Mayor Oliver Trumble</em></div>
<b>Thursday, August 23, 2007</b> &mdash; Even mayors need vacation time. Or maybe I should say, mayors <i>especially</i> need vacation time. So much happens in Millsberry daily that I hardly have time to relax and enjoy a little quiet time. I know you can relate! So, I decided to treat myself to a little island getaway in July.  <br><br>Have you ever been to Jamaica? It&#039;s a beautiful island nation with tropical weather year-round. Located in the Caribbean, it&#039;s not far from the States and English is the official language.<br>
<br>
I stayed in Montego Bay, a pretty touristy spot, but exactly what I was looking for. I enjoyed the resort atmosphere and other people who were there for the same reasons as I. I woke up each day and had nothing on the agenda! Just another day of swimming and reading a book on the beach.<br><br>One day I ventured out to Long Bay to do some surfing. I hadn&#039;t hit the waves in years, but I could still do some basic things. I wiped out a lot, but it was fun, and all the groms out there were very amused to see a guy with white hair falling every few minutes! I&#039;m glad I was able to make people laugh&mdash;I often feel I&#039;m too serious when I&#039;m in Millsberry.<br><br>As far as food goes, I enjoyed a lot of the local dishes, and I must say, they were all delicious! I&#039;d had jerk chicken before, but somehow the spices seemed all the more vibrant because I was actually in Jamaica. Jamaican beef patties, which are pastries baked with ground beef inside, were rich and absolutely addicting. The seafood I had was super fresh and served quite often in stews. A treat for the palette!<br><br>But after a week of sun, and a little sunburn (always wear sunscreen, my dear citizens!), I was happy to come home to my favorite city in the world. Millsberry was just as I&#039;d left it, nearing the end of a sweltering summer, and a rare cool breeze welcomed me back. Jamaica is a place I&#039;d highly suggest you learn more about and visit someday. I&#039;d love to go back, but right now I&#039;m just happy to be home.</div>
